  "text": "To determine whether these novel XI genes could be functionally expressed in the yeast S. cerevisiae, we assayed for xylose isomerase activity in cell extracts of S. cerevisiae harboring plasmids expressing these XI genes. The yeast strains used in this experiment are listed in Additional file 2: Table S2 . In this assay, xylose is isomerized to xylulose by the xylose isomerase present in the crude cell extracts, and the amount of xylulose produced is determined by the cysteine-carbazole-sulfuric acid method [CITATION_1] .",
